---
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';

const toc = [
  { num: '01', label: 'The question', href: '#why' },
  { num: '02', label: 'Your work', href: '#work-shift' },
  { num: '03', label: 'The barrier', href: '#barrier' },
  { num: '04', label: 'Capabilities', href: '#capabilities' },
  { num: '05', label: 'Knowledge', href: '#knowledge' },
  { num: '06', label: 'Landscape', href: '#landscape' },
];
---

<section
  id="top"
  class="relative flex min-h-[calc(100svh-61px)] flex-col px-6"
>
  <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col items-center justify-center text-center">
    <h1
      class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-7xl"
    >
      The Meta-Harness
    </h1>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-neutral-400 sm:text-2xl">
      Elevating your harness for the new era of agentic work.
    </p>
    <a
      href="#what-is"
      class="mt-12 inline-flex items-center gap-2 border border-neutral-800 px-6 py-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-neutral-300 transition-colors hover:border-neutral-600 hover:text-neutral-50"
    >
      Enter
      <span aria-hidden="true">&darr;</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div
    class="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 pb-6 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-neutral-600"
  >
    <span>Scroll down</span>
    <span aria-hidden="true">&darr;</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="what-is" class="px-6 pt-20 pb-16 md:pt-28 md:pb-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-5xl"
      >
        Your agents, beyond one repo, one session, one developer.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        Harnesses like Claude Code, Codex, and OpenCode are where React was
        before Next.js: excellent at the core, everything around it stitched
        together by hand. Next.js and TanStack Start elevated React with
        batteries included. A <mark>meta-harness</mark> does the same one layer
        up. It wraps your harness and handles what no single agent sees on its
        own: <span class="text-neutral-100"
          >coordinating changes across repositories, carrying context from
          session to session, and turning agent work into knowledge your whole
          organization can draw on</span
        >. That is this page, in order.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-5xl">
    <VizPlaceholder label="MetaHarnessLayers island" ratio="aspect-[16/10]" />
    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-center text-sm text-neutral-500">
      The shape underneath: a model predicts tokens, a harness wraps it into an
      agent that can act, the meta-harness wraps the harness.
    </p>
  </div>

  <nav aria-label="Sections" class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-5xl">
    <ul
      class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-neutral-900 bg-neutral-900 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6"
    >
      {
        toc.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <a
              href={item.href}
              class="flex h-full flex-col gap-1.5 bg-neutral-950 p-4 transition-colors hover:bg-neutral-900/60"
            >
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-neutral-600">{item.num}</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-neutral-300">{item.label}</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </nav>
</section>
